### Setup

Initialize a Node.js project and install Express:

```bash
npm init -y
npm install express
```

### Basic Server

Create an `index.js` file and set up a basic server:

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const port = 3000;

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World!');
});

app.listen(port, () => {
  console.log(`Server listening on port ${port}`);
});
```

### Nodemon for Development

Install nodemon for auto-restart on file changes:

```bash
npm install --save-dev nodemon
```

### Package.json Scripts

```json
"scripts": {
  "start": "node index.js",
  "dev": "nodemon index.js"
}
```

Run with `npm run dev` during development and `npm start` in production.

codeExample:
const express = require('express');
const app = express();
const PORT = process.env.PORT || 3000;

app.listen(PORT, () => {
  console.log(`App started on http://localhost:${PORT}`);
});
